quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  36,51,"The Trumpet will be blown ˹a second time˺, then—behold!—they will rush from the graves to their Lord"
  36,52,"They will cry, “Woe to us! Who has raised us up from our place of rest? This must be what the Most Compassionate warned us of; the messengers told the truth!”"
  36,53,"It will only take one Blast, then at once they will all be brought before Us"
  36,54,"On that Day no soul will be wronged in the least, nor will you be rewarded except for what you used to do"
  36,55,"Indeed, on that Day the residents of Paradise will be busy enjoying themselves"
  36,56,"They and their spouses will be in ˹cool˺ shade, reclining on ˹canopied˺ couches"
  36,57,There they will have fruits and whatever they desire
  36,58,And “Peace!” will be ˹their˺ greeting from the Merciful Lord
  36,59,"˹Then the disbelievers will be told,˺ “Step away ˹from the believers˺ this Day, O wicked ones"
  36,60,"Did I not command you, O Children of Adam, not to follow Satan, for he is truly your sworn enemy"
  36,61,but to worship Me ˹alone˺? This is the Straight Path
  36,62,Yet he already misled great multitudes of you. Did you not have any sense
  36,63,This is the Hell you were warned of
  36,64,Burn in it Today for your disbelief.”
  36,65,"On this Day We will seal their mouths, their hands will speak to Us, and their feet will testify to what they used to commit"
  36,66,"Had We willed, We could have easily blinded their eyes, so they would struggle to find their way. How then could they see"
  36,67,"And had We willed, We could have transfigured them on the spot, so they could neither progress forward nor turn back"